As part of efforts to ameliorate the sufferings of the vulnerable, the Women-Led Network of CSOs has today distributed packaged food to patients and their relatives at the Maryam Abacha Family Support Hospital and suspects awaiting trial at the Police CID cells, Damaturu. Chairperson of the Women-Led Network of CSOs, Barrister Altine Ibrahim said that the gesture was intended to cushion their sufferings as well as improve their livelihood “especially the less privileged in this fasting month of Ramadan”. The beneficiaries collectively expressed appreciation for the support and prayed to Allah to reward the donors abundantly.